Groovy baby ✌🏼
Buttercream sugar cookies in retro style! I can’t seem to get away from pink color palettes this year. Which design is your favorite??

How to create this whimsical 2-tone grinch frosting! 
1. Make 2 shades of green frosting. I used @americolor leaf green and mint green.
2. Layout plastic wrap. Add your frosting in as even a strip as possible. 
3. Roll up like a burrito 
4. Prepare your frosting bag with desired tip. For this design, any large circle tip will do.
5. Cut the ends off the frosting burritos.
6. Slide all your frosting colors inside your frosting bag as evenly as possible. 
7. Squeeze frosting out until all colors are coming out evenly. Now you’re ready to frost your cupcakes! 
.
.

It’s almost Saint Patrick’s Day! What’s better than Lucky Charms no chill cookies? 🍀 🌈 🎈 
These cookies are so quick, easy and delicious! 

Ingredients:
1/2 cup melted butter 
1/2 cup brown sugar
1/3 cup white sugar 
2 tsp vanilla
1 egg 
1/2 tsp baking soda 
Pinch of salt 
1 1/2 cup of flour 
1/2 cup white chocolate chips 
2/3 cup lucky charms marshmallows
1/3 cup lucky charms cereal 

Cream cooled/melted butter 2 min. Gently mix egg and vanilla. Gently mix dry ingredients until just combined. Add white chocolate chips, cereal, and marshmallows (reserve some for decorating the tops) and mix until combined. Bake on 350 for approx 10 minutes! Let me know if you have questions! 
.
.

SOUND ON! 

My three year old standing behind me *not so patiently* waiting for me to finish shooting these blackberry lavender cupcakes so he can eat them , should tell you all you need to know! 

These cupcakes are simple, and the @amoretti violet lavender extract plus fresh blackberries will have you longing for summer! 

Use code THELAVENDERCOOKIEJAR10 for 10% off the lavender collection.

For these cupcakes:

1 box of vanilla cupcake mix! Replace water with whole milk, replace oil with melted butter. Add 1 1/2 tsp @amoretti Violet Lavender Extract. Bake according to directions! 

Filling:
Two cups of fresh blackberries. I add a bit of water (about 1/3 cup- I just estimate), a squeeze of lemon and a tbsp of corn starch. Cook on stovetop on medium low until you reach the desired consistency. Stir often. *if you prefer seedless filling, run it through a fine mesh strainer!

Frosting: 
2 sticks of room temperature butter
7 cups of powdered sugar
Blackberry filling
1 1/2 tsp @amoretti Violet Lavender extract 
Whole milk 

Mix butter, powdered sugar, blackberry mixture (use the amount of your preference) and lavender extract in your mixer on low. Scrape bowl as needed. Add milk 1 tbsp at a time until you reach a creamy, manageable consistency! Enjoy! 

#amoretti #amorettibaking #amorettilavender

Welcome to spring! I’m so excited to start working with spring flavors again, and these Lavender Lemon cookies are sure to get you in the spirit! They’re infused with fresh lemon, @amoretti Violet Lavender Extract, and a dash of sunshine. ☀️ 

Use code THELAVENDERCOOKIEJAR10 for 10% off the lavender collection! 

Lavender Lemon curd cookies 

Ingredients: 
1 cup salted butter (room temperature) 
1 cup sugar 
1 egg yolk (room temperature) 
1 1/2 tbsp lemon zest 
1 tsp vanilla extract 
1 tsp Amoretti Violet Lavender Extract 
300 grams flour 
1/2 tsp baking powder 
Purple food coloring (optional)
Lemon curd 

Cream together your butter and sugar. Add egg, lemon and extracts. Mix well. Add a small
Amount of purple coloring (optional), flour, and baking powder. Mix until combined. 

Line pan with parchment paper. Form balls with approximately 2 tbsp of dough. Use a measuring spoon to create a well. Bake on 350 for 10 minutes. Reshape immediately out of the oven if needed.

When cool, pipe lemon curd into center. Enjoy! 

#amoretti #amorettiingredients #amorettibaking

My famous frosted sugar cookies, with a TWIST! These cookies are flavored with @amoretti Violet Lavender Extract! These cookies are perfect for Spring and Mother’s Day! 

Sugar cookies: 
3/4 cup sugar 
3/4 cup softened salted butter 
1 egg room temperature 
1 tsp vanilla extract 
1 tsp @amoretti Violet lavender Extract 
2 1/2 cups flour 

Cream butter and sugar. Add remaining wet ingredients and mix well. Mix in dry ingredients. Roll out on floured surface and cut into shapes. Bake on parchment lined pan 7-10 minutes on 350
 
Frosting:
1 1/4 cup salted butter 
7 cups powdered sugar 
1 1/2 tsp vanilla 
1 tsp @amoretti Violet Lavender extract 
Heavy cream 

Add butter to mixer. Mix on low, until butter loses its shape. Add powdered sugar, extracts, and 3 tbsp of heavy cream. Mix on low, scraping bowl as necessary. Add additional heavy cream 1 tbsp at a time until you reach desired consistency! Enjoy!

#amoretti #amorettilavender #amorettibaking

Hi friends! Come decorate and pack this butterfly garden cake with me! 🌸 🦋 
For this creation, I used @theofficial_kootek new cake boards and cake boxes. I’m always excited to try new packaging materials, since so many of the pastry boxes I’ve tried are so flimsy! I’m excited to report, these are 10/10. So heavy duty and sturdy. I didn’t worry about the box bending or breaking. And look how cute the window on the top is! 
This cake was so fun to make. The flowers were piped separately and frozen, so I could more easily place them on the cake without damage. I love how the colors turned out! 
.
